    <p class="headtxt1">FDI Policy in Vietnam:</p>
    <p class="plaintxt">
    <ul class="plaintxt">
  
  <li>Vietnam welcomes 100% foreign investment for the manufacturing and processing sectors by offering tax incentives on case to case basis.</li> 
   <li> As per the WTO commitment the Vietnam allows the foreign investment for the trading and service activities as follows : </li> 
</ul>
<p class="headtxt1"><img src="images/icon_2.jpg" style="padding-right: 10px;" />Trading Activities:</p>
<ul class="plaintxt">
<li>Pharmaceutical products, processed oil and crude oil, cane and beet sugar and rice are excluded from the commitment.</li>
<li>From 1st January 2008, up to 49 % foreign investment is allowed in the joint venture.</li>
<li>From 1st January 2009, 100 % foreign investment is allowed.</li>
</ul>
<p class="headtxt1"><img src="images/icon_2.jpg" style="padding-right: 10px;" />Computer related services:</p> 
<ul class="plaintxt">
<li>For the 2 years from the WTO accession , 100% foreign invested enterprises can provide services to only  foreign invested enterprises.</li>
<li>After 3 years from the WTO accession, branching is allowed.</li>
</ul> 
</p>
                
       
